    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This isn't really an RLP parsing error, more a JSON unmarshaling error? Still, I see with the blob txs, we're now using `uint256` instead of `big.Int`. Not sure we can change the other txs types at this point as it would break anyone using those types.\r\n\r\nIt does feel a bit wonky to have two different big int libraries for different txs. I don't know the best way to resolve this. Ultimately it isn't problematic in practice because the balance check will always fail.",
